[§587A-22]  Unavailability of specified privileges.  The following privileges shall not be available to exclude evidence of imminent harm, harm, or threatened harm in any proceeding under this chapter:
     (1)  The physician-patient privilege;
     (2)  The psychologist-client privilege;
     (3)  The spousal privilege; and
     (4)  The victim-counselor privilege. [L 2010, c 135, pt of §1]
